## M20a.1 negative: `?self` / `!self` sugar outside a method body.
##
## The sugar resolves to `?Self` / `!Self`, which only has a meaning
## inside a nominal (struct/enum/errors) body where `Self` is bound.
## At module-level functions, there's no enclosing nominal — the sugar
## must error rather than silently lower to something nonsensical.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error at the `?self` parameter.

fun lonely(?self) -> Int
  42

sub main()
  print(lonely(1))
